  }), "\nBy the way, in this article, the terms “coding agent” and “coding harness” are somewhat interchangeably for simplicity.\n(Strictly speaking, the agent is the model-driven decision-making loop, while the harness is the surrounding\nsoftware scaffold that provides context, tools, and execution support.)"), "\n", React.createElement(_components.p, null, "Below are six main components of coding agents."), "\n", React.createElement(_components.ol, null, "\n", React.createElement(_components.li, null, "Live Repo Context -> WorkspaceContext"), "\n", React.createElement(_components.li, null, "Prompt Shape And Cache Reuse -> build_prefix, memory_text, prompt"), "\n", React.createElement(_components.li, null, "Structured Tools, Validation, And Permissions -> build_tools, run_tool, validate_tool, approve, parse, path, tool_*"), "\n", React.createElement(_components.li, null, "Context Reduction And Output Management -> clip, history_text"), "\n", React.createElement(_components.li, null, "Transcripts, Memory, And Resumption -> SessionStore, record, note_tool, ask, reset"), "\n", React.createElement(_components.li, null, "Delegation And Bounded Subagents -> tool_delegate"), "\n"), "\n", React.createElement(_components.h3, null, "1. Live Repo Context"), "\n", React.createElement(_components.p, null, "This may be the most obvious component, but it’s also one of the most critical."), "\n", React.createElement(_components.p, null, "When a user says “fix the tests” or “implement xyz,” the model needs to understand its environment — which Git\nrepo it’s in, what branch it’s on, where relevant project documents live, and so on. These details aren’t just\nbackground noise; they directly shape what the right action looks like. “Fix the tests” is not a self-contained\ninstruction. An AGENTS.md file or project README might specify which test command to run. Knowing the repo root and\nlayout tells the agent where to look instead of where to guess."), "\n", React.createElement(_components.p, null, "Git context matters too — the current branch, uncommitted changes, and recent commits all signal what work is in\nprogress and where attention should be focused."), "\n", React.createElement(_components.p, null, "The core idea: a coding agent should gather “stable facts” about the workspace upfront, before doing anything,\nso it’s never walking into a prompt cold."), "\n", React.createElement(_components.span, {
